responses: 0: if the second (upper) house cannot block or delay legislation passed by the lower (first)
1: if the second (upper) house can only put a suspensive veto or can send for reconsideration(a "suspensive veto" is any veto that can be overridden by someone).
2: if the second (upper) house must approve must legislation or can put a final veto.
name: e_upper_block
